Verify Error Log And BMC Dump For Internal Failure
Done
Use Redfish to verify error log presence because peltool in a BMC cli command which is meant to be used by support people only.

We are just verify PEL log / type presence with through BMC dump testsuite. Does not look mandatory about the method to check this. Redfish usage for pel log generation can be verified in the dedicated pelt log generation test suite.

If you insist, you can send me : 

1. URI of PEL log info  with
2. the type of PEL ('Internal' here)
Yes please use Redfish URI. In this Redfish path you will see the error log. /redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/CELog/Entries
Done

# Wait for the BMC dump to become available and verify its presence
    Wait Until Keyword Succeeds  2 min  10 sec  Is BMC Dump Available

    ${dump_entries}=  Get BMC Dump Entries
    Should Be Equal As Integers ${len(${dump_entries})} ${1}
Done
